{
  "uid": "dnshealth-overview-demo",
  "title": "DNS Health Overview (demo)",
  "tags": [
    "dnshealth"
  ],
  "timezone": "browser",
  "editable": true,
  "graphTooltip": 0,
  "time": {
    "from": "now-15m",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "refresh": "10s",
  "schemaVersion": 42,
  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "DNS health report — ${zone}",
      "transparent": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Per-zone health snapshot inspired by intodns.com. Use the **Zone** selector at the top to switch zones.\n\n**Top row** is boolean status checks — each row's Result renders `1` as **PASS** (green) and `0` as **FAIL** (red). **Middle row** is informational — the actual records / values returned by the queries, with no PASS/FAIL coloring. **Operator / debug views** at the bottom (collapsed) include `dnshealth_soa_serial` over time, probe cycle duration, query rate, cache hit ratio, and per-zone query duration.\n\n**Demo zones in this stack:** `healthy.demo.` (all checks pass), `soa-serial-mismatch.demo.` (SOA serial divergence between primaries), `lame-nameserver.demo.` (auth NS doesn't actually serve the zone), `ns-mismatch.demo.` (parent advertises 1 NS but auth reports 2 different NSs), `missing-glue.demo.` (parent NS without glue, delegation walk fails entirely — won't appear in the selector since it produces no `dnshealth_query_success` series; the absence is the signal)."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "(count by (zone) (dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"parent\",zone=\"$zone\"}) \u003e bool 0) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "Parent has NS records for the zone",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_parent_delegation{zone=\"$zone\"} or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "Parent delegation walk succeeded",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Parent — status",
      "description": "### Parent has NS records for the zone\n\n**Metric**: `dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"parent\"}`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: The zone may be unreachable — resolvers can't find the authoritative NSs without a delegation from the parent.  \n**Investigate**: NS records (from parent) panel below; check the TLD's view of the zone.\n\n### Parent delegation walk succeeded\n\n**Metric**: `dnshealth_parent_delegation`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: The delegation walk from root failed entirely — every downstream check has no data for this zone this cycle.  \n**Investigate**: Exporter logs (`delegation walk failed`); root-server reachability.\n",
      "transparent": false,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${prometheus}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "reduce",
          "options": {
            "reducers": [
              "last"
            ],
            "mode": "seriesToRows"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "renameByName": {
              "Field": "Test",
              "Last": "Result"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "Field": 0,
              "Last": 1
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "frameIndex": 0,
        "showHeader": true,
        "showTypeIcons": false,
        "footer": {
          "show": false,
          "reducer": null,
          "countRows": false
        },
        "cellHeight": "sm"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Result"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "options": {
                      "0": {
                        "color": "red",
                        "index": 0,
                        "text": "FAIL"
                      },
                      "1": {
                        "color": "green",
                        "index": 1,
                        "text": "PASS"
                      }
                    },
                    "type": "value"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.cellOptions",
                "value": {
                  "mode": "basic",
                  "type": "color-background"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.width",
                "value": 80
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "(count by (zone) (count by (zone, nameserver) (dnshealth_query_success{check=\"soa\",zone=\"$zone\"})) \u003e= bool 2) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "Multiple authoritative nameservers (\u003e=2)",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "min by (zone) (dnshealth_query_success{check=\"soa\",zone=\"$zone\"}) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "All NSs answered SOA authoritatively",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "(max by (zone) (dnshealth_ns_recursion_available{zone=\"$zone\"}) == bool 0) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "No NS advertises recursion (RA=0)",
          "refId": "C"
        },
        {
          "expr": "((count by (zone) (group by (zone, nameserver) (dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"parent\",zone=\"$zone\"}))) == bool (count by (zone) (group by (zone, nameserver) (dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"self\",zone=\"$zone\"})))) and on(zone) (count by (zone) (dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"self\",zone=\"$zone\"}) \u003e bool 0) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "Parent and self report same NS records",
          "refId": "D"
        },
        {
          "expr": "min by (zone) (dnshealth_ns_hostname_syntax_valid{zone=\"$zone\"}) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "All NS hostnames syntactically valid (LDH)",
          "refId": "E"
        },
        {
          "expr": "((max by (zone) (dnshealth_ns_hostname_is_cname{zone=\"$zone\"})) == bool 0) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "No NS hostname is a CNAME (RFC 2181 §10.3)",
          "refId": "F"
        }
      ],
      "title": "NS — status",
      "description": "### Multiple authoritative nameservers (\u003e=2)\n\n**Metric**: distinct (zone, nameserver) tuples in `dnshealth_query_success{check=\"soa\"}`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: A single NS is a single point of failure (RFC 2182). One outage = the whole zone goes dark.  \n**Investigate**: NS records panels below; add at least one more NS.\n\n### All NSs answered SOA authoritatively\n\n**Metric**: `min(dnshealth_query_success{check=\"soa\"})`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: At least one NS isn't responding correctly; further failures take the zone dark.  \n**Investigate**: NS records (from the zone) — `Responded` column highlights which NS failed.\n\n### No NS advertises recursion (RA=0)\n\n**Metric**: `max(dnshealth_ns_recursion_available) == 0`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: Open recursive resolvers can be abused for DNS amplification / reflection attacks.  \n**Investigate**: NS records (from the zone) — `Recursion` column highlights the offending NS.\n\n### Parent and self report same NS records\n\n**Metric**: count comparison of `dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"parent\"}` vs `source=\"self\"`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: The parent's view of the NS set diverges from what the zone itself advertises; resolvers may pick a stale or wrong set.  \n**Investigate**: NS records (from parent) and NS records (from the zone) tables side-by-side.\n\n### All NS hostnames syntactically valid (LDH)\n\n**Metric**: `min(dnshealth_ns_hostname_syntax_valid)`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: Hostnames violating RFC 952 / 1123 (underscores, leading/trailing hyphens) may be rejected by strict resolvers.  \n**Investigate**: NS records tables show each NS hostname — find the one with the invalid character.\n\n### No NS hostname is a CNAME (RFC 2181 §10.3)\n\n**Metric**: `max(dnshealth_ns_hostname_is_cname) == 0`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: NS records pointing at a CNAME violate RFC 2181 §10.3; resolver handling is inconsistent → intermittent resolution failures.  \n**Investigate**: NS records tables show each NS hostname; check its CNAME chain externally.\n",
      "transparent": false,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${prometheus}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 8,
        "y": 4
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "reduce",
          "options": {
            "reducers": [
              "last"
            ],
            "mode": "seriesToRows"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "renameByName": {
              "Field": "Test",
              "Last": "Result"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "Field": 0,
              "Last": 1
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "frameIndex": 0,
        "showHeader": true,
        "showTypeIcons": false,
        "footer": {
          "show": false,
          "reducer": null,
          "countRows": false
        },
        "cellHeight": "sm"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Result"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "options": {
                      "0": {
                        "color": "red",
                        "index": 0,
                        "text": "FAIL"
                      },
                      "1": {
                        "color": "green",
                        "index": 1,
                        "text": "PASS"
                      }
                    },
                    "type": "value"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.cellOptions",
                "value": {
                  "mode": "basic",
                  "type": "color-background"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.width",
                "value": 80
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "((max by (zone) (dnshealth_soa_serial{zone=\"$zone\"}) - min by (zone) (dnshealth_soa_serial{zone=\"$zone\"})) == bool 0) and on(zone) (count by (zone) (dnshealth_soa_serial{zone=\"$zone\"}) \u003e bool 0) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "All NSs report same SOA serial",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "min by (zone) (dnshealth_soa_mname_in_ns_set{zone=\"$zone\"}) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "SOA MNAME is in zone's NS RR set",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "min by (zone) (dnshealth_soa_mname_resolves{zone=\"$zone\"}) or on() vector(0)",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "legendFormat": "SOA MNAME hostname resolves to A or AAAA",
          "refId": "C"
        }
      ],
      "title": "SOA — status",
      "description": "### All NSs report same SOA serial\n\n**Metric**: `max(dnshealth_soa_serial) - min(dnshealth_soa_serial) == 0`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: Secondaries haven't pulled the latest zone — resolvers may serve stale data depending on which NS they hit.  \n**Investigate**: SOA per-nameserver table below — find the NS reporting an out-of-date serial.\n\n### SOA MNAME is in zone's NS RR set\n\n**Metric**: `min(dnshealth_soa_mname_in_ns_set)`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: The MNAME identifies the primary master. If it's outside the NS set, NOTIFY may target the wrong server (hidden-master setups legitimately read 0 here — verify intent before alerting).  \n**Investigate**: SOA per-nameserver table — each row's `mname` label vs. the NS records tables.\n\n### SOA MNAME hostname resolves to A or AAAA\n\n**Metric**: `min(dnshealth_soa_mname_resolves)`  \n**Why FAIL matters**: NOTIFY and dynamic updates target the MNAME hostname; if it doesn't resolve, both mechanisms break silently.  \n**Investigate**: SOA per-nameserver table shows the `mname` label — try resolving that hostname externally.\n",
      "transparent": false,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${prometheus}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 4
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "reduce",
          "options": {
            "reducers": [
              "last"
            ],
            "mode": "seriesToRows"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "renameByName": {
              "Field": "Test",
              "Last": "Result"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "Field": 0,
              "Last": 1
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "frameIndex": 0,
        "showHeader": true,
        "showTypeIcons": false,
        "footer": {
          "show": false,
          "reducer": null,
          "countRows": false
        },
        "cellHeight": "sm"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Result"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "options": {
                      "0": {
                        "color": "red",
                        "index": 0,
                        "text": "FAIL"
                      },
                      "1": {
                        "color": "green",
                        "index": 1,
                        "text": "PASS"
                      }
                    },
                    "type": "value"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.cellOptions",
                "value": {
                  "mode": "basic",
                  "type": "color-background"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.width",
                "value": 80
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"parent\",zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "NS records — from parent",
      "description": "What the parent referral lists as the zone's NSs. Glue IP empty = parent did not include A glue (exporter resolved separately).",
      "transparent": false,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${prometheus}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 10,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 12
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "renameByName": {
              "ip": "Glue IP",
              "nameserver": "Nameserver"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "ip": 1,
              "nameserver": 0
            },
            "excludeByName": {
              "Time": true,
              "Value": true,
              "__name__": true,
              "instance": true,
              "job": true,
              "source": true,
              "zone": true
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "frameIndex": 0,
        "showHeader": true,
        "showTypeIcons": false,
        "sortBy": [
          {
            "displayName": "Nameserver"
          }
        ],
        "footer": {
          "show": false,
          "reducer": null,
          "countRows": false
        },
        "cellHeight": "sm"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Glue IP"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "options": {
                      "": {
                        "color": "text",
                        "index": 0,
                        "text": "(not provided)"
                      }
                    },
                    "type": "value"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_ns_record{source=\"self\",zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_query_success{check=\"soa\",zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_ns_recursion_available{zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "C"
        }
      ],
      "title": "NS records — from the zone",
      "description": "What the auth servers themselves report as the zone's NSs (source=\"self\" rows from the glue prober), joined with each NS's probe response (Responded = SOA query succeeded, Recursion = RA flag set). Empty Responded/Recursion cells mean the exporter has no probe data for that NS — happens when the auth's self-reported NS list does not match what the parent advertised, since SOA/recursion checks only run against parent-listed NSs.",
      "transparent": false,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${prometheus}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 10,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 8,
        "y": 12
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "joinByField",
          "options": {
            "byField": "nameserver",
            "mode": "outer"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "filterByValue",
          "options": {
            "filters": [
              {
                "fieldName": "Value #A",
                "config": {
                  "id": "isNotNull",
                  "options": {}
                }
              }
            ],
            "type": "include",
            "match": "all"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "renameByName": {
              "Value #B": "Responded",
              "Value #C": "Recursion",
              "ip 1": "IP",
              "nameserver": "Nameserver"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "Value #B": 2,
              "Value #C": 3,
              "ip 1": 1,
              "nameserver": 0
            },
            "excludeByName": {
              "Time 1": true,
              "Time 2": true,
              "Time 3": true,
              "Value #A": true,
              "__name__ 1": true,
              "__name__ 2": true,
              "__name__ 3": true,
              "check": true,
              "instance 1": true,
              "instance 2": true,
              "instance 3": true,
              "ip 2": true,
              "ip 3": true,
              "job 1": true,
              "job 2": true,
              "job 3": true,
              "source 1": true,
              "zone 1": true,
              "zone 2": true,
              "zone 3": true
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "frameIndex": 0,
        "showHeader": true,
        "showTypeIcons": false,
        "sortBy": [
          {
            "displayName": "Nameserver"
          }
        ],
        "footer": {
          "show": false,
          "reducer": null,
          "countRows": false
        },
        "cellHeight": "sm"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Responded"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "options": {
                      "0": {
                        "color": "red",
                        "index": 0,
                        "text": "no"
                      },
                      "1": {
                        "color": "green",
                        "index": 1,
                        "text": "yes"
                      }
                    },
                    "type": "value"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.cellOptions",
                "value": {
                  "mode": "basic",
                  "type": "color-background"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.width",
                "value": 100
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "Recursion"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "mappings",
                "value": [
                  {
                    "options": {
                      "0": {
                        "color": "green",
                        "index": 0,
                        "text": "no"
                      },
                      "1": {
                        "color": "red",
                        "index": 1,
                        "text": "RA=1"
                      }
                    },
                    "type": "value"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.cellOptions",
                "value": {
                  "mode": "basic",
                  "type": "color-background"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "custom.width",
                "value": 100
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "IP"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "custom.width",
                "value": 240
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_soa_serial{zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_soa_refresh_seconds{zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_soa_retry_seconds{zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "C"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_soa_expire_seconds{zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "D"
        },
        {
          "expr": "dnshealth_soa_minimum_seconds{zone=\"$zone\"}",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false,
          "format": "table",
          "refId": "E"
        }
      ],
      "title": "SOA — per-nameserver values",
      "description": "One row per nameserver. Empty/missing rows mean the SOA query failed for that NS.",
      "transparent": false,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${prometheus}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 10,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 12
      },
      "repeatDirection": "h",
      "transformations": [
        {
          "id": "joinByField",
          "options": {
            "byField": "nameserver",
            "mode": "outer"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "organize",
          "options": {
            "renameByName": {
              "Value #A": "Serial",
              "Value #B": "Refresh (s)",
              "Value #C": "Retry (s)",
              "Value #D": "Expire (s)",
              "Value #E": "Min TTL (s)",
              "ip 1": "IP",
              "nameserver": "Nameserver"
            },
            "indexByName": {
              "Value #A": 2,
              "Value #B": 3,
              "Value #C": 4,
              "Value #D": 5,
              "Value #E": 6,
              "ip 1": 1,
              "nameserver": 0
            },
            "excludeByName": {
              "Time 1": true,
              "Time 2": true,
              "Time 3": true,
              "Time 4": true,
              "Time 5": true,
              "__name__ 1": true,
              "__name__ 2": true,
              "__name__ 3": true,
              "__name__ 4": true,
              "__name__ 5": true,
              "instance 1": true,
              "instance 2": true,
              "instance 3": true,
              "instance 4": true,
              "instance 5": true,
              "ip 2": true,
              "ip 3": true,
